				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				First, let me say I am a privacy nut.  I won't even download free software that requires me to give personal information. But for the sake of my enjoyment of EQ I appreciate having hacking, item farming, and E-Bay style trading stopped in its tracks.<BR>
<BR>
Verant's terminology in the agreement is vague.  I would like to see some of John Smedley's commentary moved to the agreement.  I am satisfied with his explaination of what is being done, but would like to see it &quot;put into writing&quot;.  I think the customers deserve some legal protection as well.<BR>
<BR>
While they are at it, I hope that having SoftICE running is not a violation in and of itself. I regularly develop, debug and play without restarting Windows and don't want to start having to reboot to unload SoftICE to play EQ.  Also it is possible to add code to your program that tells SoftICE not to allow it to be debugged.<BR>
<BR>
I also hope they are checking for Unix debuggers GDB, DDD, etc. They have been ported to Windows and GDB is a hacking favorite.
